'''Uraiyur Mudhukootthanar''' ([[Tamil language|Tamil]]: உறையூர் முதுகூத்தனார்), also known as '''Uraiyur Mudhukootranar''', was a poet of the [[Sangam period]], to whom 9 verses of the Sangam literature have been attributed, including verse 39 of the [[Tiruvalluva Maalai]].<ref>{{cite book | last = Vedanayagam | first = Rama | author-link = | title =Tiruvalluva Maalai: Moolamum Eliya Urai Vilakkamum | publisher = Manimekalai Prasuram | series = | volume = | edition = 1 | date = 2017 | location = Chennai | pages =55–56 | language = Tamil | url = | doi = | id = | isbn = | mr = | zbl = | jfm = }}</ref>
==Biography== Uraiyur Mudhukootthanar hailed from Uraiyur and was known for his patriotism.<ref name="SangaIlakkiyam_2"/>
==Contribution to the Sangam literature== Uraiyur Mudhukootthanar has penned 9 Sangam verses, including 2 in [[Kurunthogai]], 3 in [[Agananuru]], 1 in [[Purananuru]], and 1 in [[Tiruvalluva Maalai]].<ref name="SangaIlakkiyam_2">{{cite book | last = Kowmareeshwari (Ed.) | first = S. | author-link = | title = Kurunthogai, Paripaadal, Kalitthogai | publisher = Saradha Pathippagam | series = Sanga Ilakkiyam | volume = 2 | edition = 1 | date = August 2012 | location = Chennai | pages = 423 | language = Tamil | url = | doi = | id = | isbn = | mr = | zbl = | jfm = }}</ref>
